# 🌡️ Temperature Converter App

This is a simple and responsive Temperature Converter application built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It allows users to convert temperatures between Celsius, Fahrenheit, and Kelvin in real-time.

## 🚀 Features

- Convert between:
  - Celsius (°C)
  - Fahrenheit (°F)
  - Kelvin (K)
- Real-time conversion as the user types
- Dropdowns to select input and output units
- Clean, mobile-friendly interface custom CSS
- Error handling for invalid input

## 🔗 Live Demo

👉 [Live Demo](https://temperature-converter-app-mu.vercel.app/)  

## 🛠 Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3
- JavaScript (Vanilla)

## 📦 Installation

1. Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/CharlesFaye/temperature-converter-app.git

2. Navigate into the folder
cd temperature-converter-app

3. Open index.html in your browser
(or use Live Server in VS Code)

🧠 How It Works
. User enters a temperature in one unit (e.g., °C).

. JavaScript listens for input events and applies conversion formulas:

    . °F = (°C × 9/5) + 32

    . K = °C + 273.15

    . etc.

. The result is displayed instantly in the selected output unit.

. Input validation ensures only numbers are processed.

🗂️ Project Structure
temperature-converter/
├── index.html        # Main layout
├── script.js         # Conversion logic
└── style.css         # Custom styling 

🔧 Optional Features
. Dark mode toggle

. Convert automatically when changing unit types

. Swap input and output units with one click

. Support for decimals and rounding preferences

